The '''Sula cuckoo-dove''' ('''''Turacoena sulaensis'''''), is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Columbidae]].
It is [[endemic]] to the [[Sula Islands]] and the [[Banggai Islands Regency|Banggai Archipelago]] in [[Indonesia]]. Prior to 2016, it was considered a subspecies of the [[white-faced cuckoo dove]].

